This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with improving wireless data rates through the deployment of more access points. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the theoretical optimal multiplexing gain. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a novel scheme for synchronization. The paper also mentions the use of FPGA, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
